        "text": "## La³⁺ Complexes with Carboxylic Acid Ligands — Most Stable\n\nAll values are **log β₁** for the 1:1 reaction **La³⁺ + L ⇌ LaL**, aqueous solution.\n\n| Rank | Ligand | Abbreviation | Class | log β₁ | T (°C) | I (M) |\n|------|--------|--------------|-------|--------|--------|-------|\n| 1 | Ethylenedinitrilo-N,N,N′,N′-tetraacetic acid | **EDTA** | Aminopolycarboxylic acid | **15.5** | 25 | 0.1 |\n| 2 | Nitrilotriacetic acid | **NTA** | Aminopolycarboxylic acid | **11.0–11.34** | 20–25 | 0.1 |\n| 3 | Ethylenedinitrilo-N,N′-di(3-propanoic)-N,N′-diacetic acid | **EDTAP** | Aminopolycarboxylic acid | **10.78** | 25 | 0.1 |\n| 4 | Ethylenediiminodiacetic acid | **EDDA** | Aminopolycarboxylic acid | **8.6** | 25 | 0.1 |\n| 5 | Pyridine-2,6-dicarboxylic acid | **Dipicolinic acid** | Pyridinecarboxylic acid | **7.9** | 25 | 0.5 |\n\n> **Source:** NIST SRD-46, metal_79 (La³⁺), beta_totN_30 equilibrium definition (M + L ⇌ ML).",
